The following issues were recently filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission: 

ECI Environmental Inc., initial offering of 1.1 million common shares, of which 990,000 shares will be sold by ECI and the rest by holders, via Oppenheimer & Co. 

Figgie International Inc., offering of $175 million face amount of senior notes, via Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. 

J. Baker Inc., offering of 1.5 million common shares, of which one million will be offered by the company and 500,000 will be offered by holders, via PaineWebber Inc., Alex Brown & Sons, Inc., and Smith Barney, Harris Upham & Co, Inc. 

Jan Bell Marketing Inc., proposed public offering of three million common shares, of which 2,640,000 are to be sold by the company and 360,000 by holders, via Goldman, Sachs & Co., Morgan Stanley & Co. Inc., Salomon Brothers Inc., and Oppenheimer. 

Rio Finance Corp., a subsidiary of MarCor Resorts L.P.V, offering of $110 million face amount of first mortgage bonds, via PaineWebber. 

UnionFed Financial Corp., registration statement on the proposed redemption of all 7-1/4 convertible subordinated debentures due 2011. 

